WEBVTT

00:01:06.542 --> 00:01:08.625
Asuna... Asuna!

00:02:02.125 --> 00:02:08.083
I've... become such a crybaby, Asuna.

00:02:10.583 --> 00:02:16.042
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:02:16.042 --> 00:02:21.417
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:31.708 --> 00:02:42.083
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:02:42.292 --> 00:02:52.833
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:02:52.917 --> 00:02:58.125
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:02:58.125 --> 00:03:01.958
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:03:03.042 --> 00:03:08.292
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:13.333
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:19.000
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:03:19.083 --> 00:03:25.208
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:03:27.083 --> 00:03:33.625
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:03:39.042 --> 00:03:43.042
"Return"

00:03:50.625 --> 00:03:54.250
We don't look alike after all, do we?

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:06.125
Big Brother... I'm off to practice.

00:04:53.208 --> 00:04:54.917
Morning, Sugu.

00:04:58.458 --> 00:05:00.167
M-Morning...

00:05:02.375 --> 00:05:06.583
Honestly... If you were watching,
you should've said something.

00:05:06.583 --> 00:05:10.542
Well... you were just so into it.

00:05:10.958 --> 00:05:15.167
I wasn't really. It's just a habit now.

00:05:16.333 --> 00:05:17.750
I see...

00:05:18.667 --> 00:05:22.000
You've kept it up all this time, right?

00:05:22.417 --> 00:05:23.875
It's light.

00:05:24.875 --> 00:05:28.375
That's timber bamboo,
so it's pretty heavy.

00:05:29.833 --> 00:05:35.917
Well, not as much as I imagined...
Or relatively speaking I mean...

00:05:40.458 --> 00:05:43.375
What are you comparing it to?

00:05:45.417 --> 00:05:48.125
Hey, want to give it a go?

00:05:48.125 --> 00:05:51.208
A go? You mean a match?

00:05:51.208 --> 00:05:52.208
Yeah.

00:05:52.667 --> 00:05:55.625
A real one with protective gear?

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.833
We could stop short of contact...

00:05:58.833 --> 00:06:02.958
I mean, I'd feel bad
if I hurt you right off.

00:06:03.625 --> 00:06:08.458
We still have Grandfather's
gear, right? Let's do it in the dojo.

00:06:09.250 --> 00:06:13.500
It's been two years, but you
sound pretty confident, don't you?

00:06:13.500 --> 00:06:18.708
I was top eight in the middle-school
nationals. Think you stand a chance?

00:06:19.167 --> 00:06:24.542
Also, are you sure you feel up to it?
You shouldn't overdo it...

00:06:27.375 --> 00:06:32.375
I'll show you the results of the rehab
I've been doing at the gym every day.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.542
What's that, Big Brother?

00:06:48.542 --> 00:06:52.333
It's okay. It's my
own style of swordplay.

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.333
--Let's go.
--Okay.

00:06:59.583 --> 00:07:03.542
<i>His head's open.</i>
<i>I'll strike him there and...</i>

00:07:05.375 --> 00:07:06.750
<i>Huh?</i>

00:07:07.875 --> 00:07:10.708
<i>Somehow, he looks imposing.</i>

00:07:18.792 --> 00:07:20.250
<i>In that case...</i>

00:07:46.708 --> 00:07:49.500
A-Are you okay, Big Brother?

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:55.667
Man, I lost.
You sure are strong, Sugu.

00:07:55.917 --> 00:07:58.958
You'd put Heathcliff to shame...

00:07:58.958 --> 00:08:01.000
Are you really okay?

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:02.292
Yeah.

00:08:02.292 --> 00:08:04.583
Let's call it a day.

00:08:16.583 --> 00:08:21.417
--D-Did I hit your head too hard?
--N-No, it's years of habit...

00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:27.500
The footwork was
one thing, but those attacks...

00:08:27.500 --> 00:08:32.167
Guess I can't recreate my sword
skills without help from the system...

00:08:32.167 --> 00:08:37.250
I have to say you surprised me.
Since when have you been practicing?

00:08:37.250 --> 00:08:38.750
Oh, you know...

00:08:38.750 --> 00:08:43.542
But it is fun after all.
Maybe I'll take it up again... kendo.

00:08:43.542 --> 00:08:45.667
Really? Seriously?

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:48.583
Sugu, will you teach me?

00:08:48.583 --> 00:08:50.375
O-Of course!

00:08:50.625 --> 00:08:53.250
Let's train together again!

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:56.500
When I regain
a little more muscle, okay?

00:08:59.375 --> 00:09:02.750
Actually, Big Brother, I've also...

00:09:04.833 --> 00:09:09.125
--Nope, I think I'll keep it a secret.
--What's up with that?

00:09:12.667 --> 00:09:15.250
What are you doing today?

00:09:16.625 --> 00:09:20.250
Today I'm going to the hospital...

00:09:23.208 --> 00:09:24.292
I see.

00:09:25.208 --> 00:09:28.500
You're going to see her, aren't you?

00:09:29.833 --> 00:09:32.000
Asuna, was it?

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:37.458
Yeah. Since that's the only thing
that I can do for her...

00:09:39.042 --> 00:09:44.958
All right, it's my turn to make breakfast,
so you go take a shower first, Sugu.

00:09:52.875 --> 00:09:58.958
<i>Two months ago, I defeated</i>
<i>Heathcliff and cleared the death game.</i>

00:10:00.625 --> 00:10:05.583
<i>As soon as I woke up, in exchange</i>
<i>for information on SAO, I asked</i>

00:10:05.583 --> 00:10:09.542
<i>an official of the Internal Affairs</i>
<i>Ministry's SAO task force</i>

00:10:09.542 --> 00:10:11.708
<i>for Asuna's location.</i>

00:10:18.792 --> 00:10:20.833
<i>What I learned</i>

00:10:20.833 --> 00:10:25.667
<i>was that she was placed in</i>
<i>Tokorozawa General Hospital in Saitama.</i>

00:10:25.667 --> 00:10:28.083
"Asuna Yuki"

00:10:29.042 --> 00:10:35.333
<i>And that approximately 300 players,</i>
<i>including Asuna, had yet to wake up.</i>

00:10:41.083 --> 00:10:42.375
<i>The public</i>

00:10:42.375 --> 00:10:47.958
<i>is clamoring that the missing Akihiko</i>
<i>Kayaba's conspiracy is still in play.</i>

00:10:49.167 --> 00:10:52.833
<i>The SAO incident still isn't over.</i>

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:07.333
Asuna...

00:11:16.083 --> 00:11:21.542
Oh, you're here, Kirigaya.
Thank you for visiting so often.

00:11:21.542 --> 00:11:24.875
Hello. Sorry to bother you, Mr. Yuki.

00:11:25.167 --> 00:11:30.167
No, you can come whenever you like.
It makes my daughter happy.

00:11:37.125 --> 00:11:38.625
President...

00:11:40.958 --> 00:11:43.750
Oh, you've never met, have you?

00:11:44.042 --> 00:11:47.875
This is our laboratory chief, Sugou.

00:11:47.875 --> 00:11:51.667
I'm Nobuyuki Sugou.
Nice to meet you.

00:11:51.667 --> 00:11:54.208
I'm Kazuto Kirigaya.

00:11:54.708 --> 00:11:58.208
Really? So you're the hero Kirito?

00:11:59.333 --> 00:12:04.417
Oh, sorry. We can't disclose what
happened inside the SAO server, right?

00:12:05.125 --> 00:12:11.583
He's the son of my right-hand man, you see...
He's always been like family.

00:12:12.458 --> 00:12:19.250
Sir, about that,
I'd like to make it official.

00:12:20.708 --> 00:12:25.083
I see... But are you sure about this?

00:12:25.083 --> 00:12:28.792
You're still young.
You could start a new life.

00:12:28.792 --> 00:12:32.208
My heart has long been set.

00:12:33.083 --> 00:12:37.000
While she's as beautiful as
she is now, I'd like Asuna

00:12:37.750 --> 00:12:40.083
to wear the dress.

00:12:41.708 --> 00:12:43.875
You have a point...

00:12:44.333 --> 00:12:48.917
It might be about time
for us to prepare ourselves...

00:12:50.917 --> 00:12:55.375
I'm sorry to cut our conversation short,
but I have a meeting.

00:12:55.375 --> 00:13:00.792
We can continue this another time.
Kirigaya, I'll see you again.

00:13:11.375 --> 00:13:16.167
Is it true that within that game,
you were living with Asuna?

00:13:16.792 --> 00:13:17.792
Yes...

00:13:17.792 --> 00:13:23.375
Then I suppose that complicates
our relationship somewhat, doesn't it?

00:13:31.292 --> 00:13:37.333
What we were just discussing,
you see... was Asuna's marriage to me.

00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:43.500
There's no way you can do that...

00:13:43.500 --> 00:13:47.667
Indeed. Since we can't
legally register our marriage,

00:13:47.667 --> 00:13:52.708
I'm simply going to be adopted
into the Yuki family on paper.

00:13:52.708 --> 00:13:58.417
The truth is that this girl
has always disliked me.

00:13:58.958 --> 00:14:01.583
Our parents don't know that.

00:14:01.583 --> 00:14:06.500
But if it ever came to marriage,
it's quite likely that she'd reject me.

00:14:06.500 --> 00:14:11.625
So in my eyes,
this situation is extremely fortunate...

00:14:12.667 --> 00:14:14.125
Stop it.

00:14:18.208 --> 00:14:23.500
Are you trying to take advantage
of the fact that she's in a coma?

00:14:23.500 --> 00:14:28.667
Take advantage?
No, it's a legitimate right.

00:14:29.708 --> 00:14:31.917
Listen, Kirigaya.

00:14:33.333 --> 00:14:38.375
Do you know what happened to Argus,
the developer of SAO?

00:14:38.833 --> 00:14:41.208
I heard it was dissolved.

00:14:41.208 --> 00:14:42.458
Yes.

00:14:43.042 --> 00:14:48.292
The development costs and massive
damages they were forced to pay

00:14:48.292 --> 00:14:50.375
bankrupted them.

00:14:50.375 --> 00:14:54.375
And the maintenance of
the SAO servers was entrusted

00:14:54.375 --> 00:15:00.750
to electronics maker RCT,
whose CEO is Shozo Yuki.

00:15:02.125 --> 00:15:07.000
And I work for its full-dive
technology research division.

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:13.417
In other words, you could say
I'm the one who's keeping Asuna alive.

00:15:14.167 --> 00:15:20.042
So I can ask for a little something
by way of compensation, can't I?

00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:25.750
I don't know what sort of promises
you made to her in the game.

00:15:25.750 --> 00:15:29.833
But I don't want you
to ever come back here.

00:15:29.833 --> 00:15:34.000
I'd also have you refrain from
any contact with the Yuki family.

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:39.667
The ceremony will be held in this
hospital room in a week, on January 26th.

00:15:39.667 --> 00:15:42.917
Too bad it's not an auspicious day,

00:15:42.917 --> 00:15:46.958
but I want you to have a little piece
of my happiness, so I'll invite you.

00:15:47.333 --> 00:15:52.500
Lament your final goodbye, Mr. Hero.

00:15:59.792 --> 00:16:03.083
Big Brother? The bath's free now.

00:16:10.625 --> 00:16:14.125
Big Brother! If you're here,
at least answer!

00:16:14.125 --> 00:16:17.750
You didn't even turn on
the heat. What's wrong?

00:16:21.625 --> 00:16:25.958
Sorry. Could you
leave me alone for a while?

00:16:25.958 --> 00:16:28.583
But it's so cold in here...

00:16:29.417 --> 00:16:31.417
Wh-What's wrong?

00:16:32.083 --> 00:16:33.458
It's nothing.

00:16:33.458 --> 00:16:36.917
But... You're freezing...

00:16:36.917 --> 00:16:41.292
You'll catch a cold.
You should take a bath.

00:16:43.750 --> 00:16:46.125
I'm hopeless.

00:16:46.875 --> 00:16:52.542
I swore I wouldn't show any weakness
around you, no matter what...

00:16:56.542 --> 00:17:01.958
Did something
happen to her? To Asuna?

00:17:05.042 --> 00:17:08.917
Asuna's going someplace far away...

00:17:09.708 --> 00:17:13.208
Where I'll never
be able to reach her...

00:17:31.250 --> 00:17:34.417
Don't give up.

00:17:34.417 --> 00:17:39.667
Don't give up so easily
on the one you love.

00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:51.375
<i>I'm not going to lie</i>
<i>to myself anymore, either.</i>

00:17:59.208 --> 00:18:04.667
I remember it like it was yesterday.
When Kazuto, out of the blue,

00:18:04.667 --> 00:18:09.417
said that he wanted me
to tell him about his real parents.

00:18:09.417 --> 00:18:12.083
I was really surprised then!

00:18:12.083 --> 00:18:13.917
He was still 10,

00:18:13.917 --> 00:18:19.167
but he noticed the deleted record
on the citizens' registration network.

00:18:19.792 --> 00:18:23.375
Jeez, that sounds like him, doesn't it?

00:18:23.375 --> 00:18:27.208
I was so surprised
I forgot to feign ignorance.

00:18:27.208 --> 00:18:32.583
So I blurted out that my sister and
her husband were his real parents.

00:18:36.208 --> 00:18:38.250
Hey, Mom.

00:18:38.250 --> 00:18:39.500
What?

00:18:40.042 --> 00:18:43.042
Do you think that's connected

00:18:43.042 --> 00:18:48.750
to him constantly playing online
games ever since middle school?

00:18:48.750 --> 00:18:50.667
Not at all.

00:18:50.667 --> 00:18:56.917
After all, by age six, he'd already built
his own machine out of junk parts.

00:18:57.208 --> 00:19:02.833
If anything, he inherited my
computer-geek genes. At least mentally.

00:19:04.792 --> 00:19:10.792
All right, I'm heading home now.
Don't stay too long, Suguha.

00:19:10.792 --> 00:19:12.625
Yeah, okay.

00:19:17.917 --> 00:19:19.958
Happy birthday.

00:19:27.292 --> 00:19:33.333
<i>I still can't really believe my</i>
<i>big brother and I are actually cousins.</i>

00:19:37.083 --> 00:19:38.708
Big Brother...

00:20:05.458 --> 00:20:08.917
<i>But your heart...</i>

00:20:15.208 --> 00:20:20.333
<i>Your heart... belongs to her alone.</i>

00:20:31.417 --> 00:20:34.250
Hey, wake up, Sugu.

00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:36.625
It's morning, you know.

00:20:43.292 --> 00:20:45.250
I said wake up...

00:20:45.250 --> 00:20:48.583
You won't have time
for morning practice.

00:20:54.833 --> 00:20:57.500
Morning, Big Brother...

00:20:57.500 --> 00:20:58.917
Morning.

00:21:08.708 --> 00:21:09.917
Morning.

00:21:17.917 --> 00:21:20.875
Um... I-I...

00:21:26.917 --> 00:21:28.292
Jeez...

00:21:33.625 --> 00:21:35.750
Don't give up.

00:21:38.417 --> 00:21:40.875
Yeah, she's right.

00:21:44.458 --> 00:21:48.167
"You have new mail"

00:21:53.917 --> 00:21:56.375
"Subject: Look at this!!"
"Sender: Agil"

00:21:58.708 --> 00:22:00.333
What is this?

00:22:14.875 --> 00:22:16.208
Asuna!

00:22:17.917 --> 00:22:25.000
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:34.875
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.083 --> 00:22:52.875
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.208 --> 00:23:00.083
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.375 --> 00:23:07.250
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.417 --> 00:23:15.167
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.167 --> 00:23:22.083
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.083 --> 00:23:29.292
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.292 --> 00:23:36.708
<i>Carrying the passion</i>
<i>I've lit in my heart</i>

00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:44.917
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:23:47.042 --> 00:23:53.152
Next Time: "Land of the Fairies."
